name: Tugu Singa Ambara Raja
address: Jl. Ngurah Rai, Banjar Paketan, Paket Agung, Kec. Buleleng, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81118, Indonesia
review 1: The icon of Singaraja City, northern part of Bali. Located inside a busy T-Junction, right in front of Buleleng Mayoral Office. Not exactly a place you can stop, just seeing through whenever you pass by. Overall, looks majestic
review 2:
This monument is a symbol of the city of Buleleng.
This monument was built to commemorate the might of Ki Gusti Ngurah Panji Sakti, who was the ruler of the northern region of the island of the Gods in the 1660s.
The statue is a winged lion statue that grips a shepherd corn that symbolizes the strength, knights, power of the brave Balinese leader.  This statue is supported by a lotus flower shaped pillar.
Located in the city center of Singaraja.

review 1: More like "Slow Pizza". It took them more than 30 minutes to prepare a small size pizza. I came with my family sitting there to eat. After 15 minutes, the drinks came. We waited too long until there was no reason left to eat there. Maybe because it's the only pizzeria cafe in town. They prioritized the pizzas for delivery more than their customers at the table.
review 2: Very nice place to hangout and relaxing music. Atmosphere is good. Child friendly, friendly service aww
review 3: Nice place, favourite place to get pizza, the only thing is that you should plan ahead if you wanna order since it takes quite a time to get delivered.
review 4: The workers there look like they don't want to take your order and just say it takes 45 minutes to get any pizza. Just go somewhere else you don't have to waste your 45 minutes.
